This is a simple and healthy dish that comes together very quickly and tastes great. I made it as written using arugula, but I did use just half the amount of olive oil called for. In the future, I think I would saute the shallots and tomatoes in the oil first and then add the lemon juice and capers. I think that would enhance the flavor even more. I served it with a chickpea salad with kalamata olives, herbs, olive oil, onions. Good combination.

