I took some liberties with this recipe. First was a 14.5 ounce can of diced tomatoes, drained. Then I doubled the amount of arugula (the garden is producing a whole poop-load this year---a cleaned up version of an official unit of Southern measurement). Next, two 6 ounce salmon fillets for just the Fair Maiden and myself. And, finally---presentation! (I've been watching a lot of Great Chefs of the World this year since getting laid-off due to the Bush economic reforms). The salmon demanded to be served on top of the arugula mixture with a bit of lemon juice and the lemon slices for garnish---sliced to the center and slightly twisted.

